      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Setting `HeapEnableTerminationOnCorruption` seems like a sensible idea (trusting that it doesn't generate false positives like some of the debug memory monitoring tools).\r\n\r\nBut why remove the `SetProcessDEPPolicy(PROCESS_DEP_ENABLE);` call? It still has an effect on x86 builds. Or is this in anticipation of deprecating x86 support?",
